hand. She wears a beige trench-style coat over a light top. Her long blonde hair falls loosely around her shoulders. Large white text with a lavender block behind part of it reads “FULLER-LOOKING BROWS” at the lower left. As she faces forward, her brows are prominent and neatly shaped. The view moves closer to her face, keeping the subway doors, poles, and purple advertisement panels behind her.\n\nA hand with dark-painted nails holds the Maybelline Express Brow Duo horizontally, showing the slim black-and-lavender tool. On-screen text at the lower left reads “JUST TWO STEPS.” The product is then shown in detail: one end has an angled, slanted brow pencil tip in a brown shade, shaped like a tiny wedge for drawing precise lines.\n\nThe blonde woman demonstrates the first step inside the subway car. Text at the upper left reads “STEP 1 DEFINE,” with a black circle containing the number “1.” She holds a small mirror or phone in one hand near a yellow subway pole and uses the pencil end of the brow tool with the other hand. She carefully traces along the upper edge of one eyebrow. Her blue-grey nail polish is visible as she guides the pencil. In a close-up, the angled pencil tip touches the outer arch of her brow, darkening and sharpening the line while her eye looks downward in concentration.\n\nThe product’s second end is then shown close up. Text reads “STEP 2 FILL,” with the number “2” in a black circle. The applicator is a small rounded sponge tip loaded with brown powder, attached to a glossy black barrel with a white collar. It is shown beside the angled pencil tip, visually distinguishing the two ends of the duo.\n\nThe dark-skinned woman with the neon hoodie demonstrates the filling step. First, she is seen through a reflective subway window, raising the applicator toward her brow. Then in a close-up, she applies the sponge tip along her eyebrow, filling in sparse areas with the brown powder. Her face is angled slightly upward, eyes looking toward the brow she is working on, and her skin has a smooth, highlighted finish. The text “STEP 2 FILL” remains at the upper left.\n\nA close-up of her face follows with a lavender label reading “BEFORE” near the lower left. Her expression is neutral and steady as she looks forward. Then the label changes to “AFTER” on a lavender bar near the lower right. Her brows appear more defined and filled, especially across the arch and tail, while the rest of her makeup remains natural and polished.\n\nThe commercial returns to the product display over the moving silver subway background. The long brow duo lies across the top, and the black applicator with the rounded powder tip appears lower left, both framing the large central text “NEW EXPRESS BROW DUO” on the lavender band. The product shifts position slightly as the display repeats, again emphasizing the tan pencil end and the black sponge applicator end. The final image returns to the lavender band with “MAYBELLINE” in bold black letters and “NEW YORK” beneath it, set over the blurred metallic subway exterior.",
